The Presidential Memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on March 29, 2016, establishes the Mental Health and Substance Use Disorder Parity Task Force. The task force is responsible for identifying and promoting best practices for compliance with and implementation of requirements related to mental health and substance use disorder parity. It will also address gaps in guidance, particularly in regards to substance use disorder parity. The task force will coordinate efforts across various agencies and conduct outreach to stakeholders such as patients, healthcare providers, insurers, and state regulators. A report on the findings and recommendations of the task force is to be presented to the President by October 31, 2016, and made public. The memorandum also includes general provisions regarding the assistance and information provided by agencies, the authority of executive departments, and the implementation of the memorandum in accordance with applicable law.